body: definitely our bug, thanks for reporting!
this task will get someone's attention soon
@carlosmiranda this is your task now, please help

@yegor256 , as far as I know, we normally don't handle `null` in our API, however, we may need to do so here. How would you suggest going about it, just remove the `@NotNull` check and pass the result back? Or do you have something else in mind?
Important note: the returned value from the Java JSON implementation is actually `JsonValue.NULL`, not `null`.

I think we should add method `hasName()` and let `name()` throw an exception, as it does now. NULL is a bad practice, no matter what Github is thinking about it :) see http://www.yegor256.com/2014/05/13/why-null-is-bad.html
Fix has been submitted at pull request #819 and ready for review.
@kenzierocks , this feature has been implemented in #819 , can we close this now?
This feature is released to Maven Central in [version 0.9](https://github.com/jcabi/jcabi-github/releases/tag/jcabi-0.9)
